---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Pitching at Warsaw Startup Stage | Francisco Cucullu" description="International startup pitch competition in Warsaw, Poland, presenting to investors and industry leaders.">
    <article class="wrapper">
        <a href="/blog" class="back">&larr; Back</a>

        <header class="article-header">
            <span class="tag">Pitch</span>
            <h1>Pitching at Warsaw Startup Stage</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Competing in an international startup pitch competition in Warsaw, Poland.</p>
            <p class="meta">By Francisco Cucullu &middot; AI Product Leader</p>
        </header>

        <div class="content">
            <p>I traveled to Warsaw, Poland, to compete in an international startup pitch competition. The event brought together founders from across Europe, each presenting their companies to a panel of investors and industry leaders.</p>

            <p>Pitching internationally forces you to strip away local context and communicate your value proposition in universal terms. What works in your home market may not resonate with investors who have never heard of your industry's local dynamics. The discipline of making your pitch work for a global audience is one of the most valuable exercises a founder can go through.</p>

            <div class="video-wrapper">
                <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6BX8Vtu2Jj8" title="Warsaw Startup Pitch" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>

            <p>Warsaw's startup ecosystem is growing fast. The city has a strong technical talent pool, competitive costs, and increasing venture capital activity. Competing there gave me exposure to a different investor mindset and a broader European perspective on what makes a startup fundable.</p>

            <p>The experience reinforced something I believe strongly: the best pitches are not about the product. They are about the problem, the market, and why your team is the one to solve it.</p>
        </div>

        
            <div class="photo-grid">
                <img src="/assets/speaking-1779160587594-AQADYgxrG04GYER-.jpg" alt="Francisco Cucullu speaking" />
                <img src="/assets/speaking-1779160592377-AQADYwxrG04GYER-.jpg" alt="Francisco Cucullu speaking" />
            </div>

        <div class="article-links">
            <a href="/speaking/warsaw" class="link-button">View event page</a>
        </div>

        <footer class="article-footer">
            <p>Francisco Cucullu is an AI Product Leader building AI products at scale. <a href="/">Learn more</a>.</p>
        </footer>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .wrapper {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }

    .back {
        color: #a855f7;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .article-header {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .tag {
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
        border-radius: 999rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        background: var(--accent-regular);
        color: var(--accent-text-over);
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: var(--text-3xl);
        color: var(--gray-0);
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .subtitle {
        font-size: var(--text-lg);
        color: var(--gray-300);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .meta {
        color: var(--gray-400);
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
    }

    .content {
        color: var(--gray-200);
        line-height: 1.8;
        font-size: var(--text-md);
    }

    .content h2 {
        font-size: var(--text-2xl);
        color: var(--gray-0);
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .content p {
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }

    .content a {
        color: #a855f7;
    }

    .video-wrapper {
        position: relative;
        padding-bottom: 56.25%;
        height: 0;
        overflow: hidden;
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .video-wrapper iframe {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
    }

    .article-links {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .link-button {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        background: var(--accent-regular);
        color: var(--accent-text-over);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
        transition: opacity 0.2s;
    }

    .link-button:hover {
        opacity: 0.85;
    }

    
    .photo-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 1rem;
        margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }

    .photo-grid img {
        width: 100%;
        border-radius: 0.75rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--gray-800);
        object-fit: cover;
        aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
    }

    .article-footer {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        padding-top: 2rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-800);
        color: var(--gray-400);
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
    }

    .article-footer a {
        color: #a855f7;
    }

    @media (min-width: 50em) {
        h1 {
            font-size: var(--text-4xl);
        }
    }
</style>
